{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_jbyMK6gcvDBiY2XbPhnc3oYF","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# `space/` — space format\n2\t\n3\tA **space** is a directory bundle of AI specialists (**agents**) plus the tooling they reference; `loadSpace(dir)` reads it into a `Space` record of `{agents, tasklists, functions, components, knowledge}` (and `dependentSpaces`) `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts#loadSpace`. A space must have an `agents/` directory with at least one agent subdirectory, unless the caller passes `requireAgents:false` (function-only system spaces) `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:586-603`. Each agent is a persona plus deterministic `functions/`, load-on-demand `knowledge/`, DAG `tasklists/`, agent-rendered `components/`, and typed `events/` emitter defs — all resolved by name against the sibling directories of the same space `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:652-719`.\n4\t\n5\t## Where spaces live\n6\t\n7\tSpaces resolve from exactly **two roots**, and every session build consults both: the **system** root `<root>/system/spaces/` (`listSystemSpaceDirs`) and the **project** root `<root>/<projectId>/spaces/` (`listProjectSpaceDirs`) `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/projects.ts:141-159` · `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/session-manager.ts:1170-1175`. `<root>` is the persistent runtime root — `<cwd>/.lmthing`, or `LMTHING_ROOT` when set, so the compute pod can persist onto its data volume `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/cli/bin.ts#resolveLmthingRoot`; the default project id is `user` `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/projects.ts#DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID`, while `system` is a *synthetic* project id that maps to `<root>/system/` rather than a real project directory `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/projects.ts:24-31`. Both roots are materialized on pod boot: every system space shipped with `@lmthing/core` is copied into `<root>/system/spaces/<name>/` `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts#materializeRuntime`, and the default user project skeleton creates `<root>/user/spaces/` `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts:112-115`. A space can also be **nested inside a project** — e.g. `store/projects/blog/spaces/newsroom/` ships with the `blog` app `store/projects/blog/spaces/newsroom/agents/researcher/instruct.md`. Spaces are **distributed through the store catalog** under `store/spaces/`, today mostly integrations (e.g. `store/spaces/integration-slack/`) `store/spaces/integration-slack/package.json:1-5`.\n8\t\n9\t## Directory layout\n10\t\n11\t```\n12\t<space>/\n13\t├── package.json            # store spaces only: the `lmthing` manifest block               → package.json.md\n14\t├── README.md               # human docs (not read by the loader)\n15\t├── agents/                 # the AI specialists (required unless requireAgents:false)       → agents/\n16\t│   └── <agent-slug>/\n17\t│       ├── charter.md      # fork-safe identity/guardrails (body only, no frontmatter)\n18\t│       └── instruct.md     # YAML frontmatter (config) + operating-instructions body\n19\t├── functions/              # deterministic TS helpers callable by agents (no LLM)           → functions/\n20\t│   └── <fnName>.ts\n21\t├── components/             # agent-rendered UI                                              → components/\n22\t│   ├── view/<Name>.tsx     # display components (used with display())\n23\t│   └── form/<Name>.tsx     # interactive inputs (used with ask())\n24\t├── tasklists/              # DAG workflows an action runs                                    → tasklists/\n25\t│   └── <tasklist-slug>/\n26\t│       ├── index.md        # frontmatter (input, connections) + overview body\n27\t│       └── NN-<task-id>.md # numbered steps, sorted lexically (NN-<id>.ts = code node)\n28\t├── knowledge/              # structured, load-on-demand domain docs                          → knowledge/\n29\t│   └── <domain>/<field>/\n30\t│       ├── index.md        # frontmatter (type, variable, default, description) + overview\n31\t│       └── <aspect>.md     # one aspect each (every .md except index.md)\n32\t├── events/                 # typed emitter defs — makes the space an EVENT SOURCE           → events/\n33\t│   └── <name>.ts\n34\t└── hooks/                  # (optional) event-hook consumers, {type:'event'}                → hooks/\n35\t    └── <slug>.ts\n36\t```\n37\t\n38\tNot every directory is required. The `agents/` walk skips non-directory entries and each other loader returns empty when its directory is absent, so a space can omit any of `functions/`, `components/`, `knowledge/`, `tasklists/` `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:173,213-215,259-261,359`. For example the Slack integration ships `agents/ functions/ events/ knowledge/` with **no** `tasklists/` or `components/` `store/spaces/integration-slack/package.json:1-3`, while the `newsroom` space ships `agents/ functions/ components/ tasklists/ knowledge/` with **no** `events/` `store/projects/blog/spaces/newsroom/agents/researcher/instruct.md:1-2`. `package.json` is read only for its `name` and dependency list (npm install runs only when deps are declared) `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:606-650`; its `lmthing` manifest block is used by the store, and project-nested spaces like `newsroom` have no `package.json` at all `store/spaces/integration-slack/package.json:4-19`.\n39\t\n40\t**A model does not write these files directly** — there is no generic filesystem on any agent's surface. A space's files are authored through the **architect's typed builder functions**, which are space-rooted through `resolveSpaceDir` and typecheck the source before writing: `writeAgentFile`/`writeFunctionFile`/`writeComponentFile`/`writeTaskFile`/`writeKnowledgeIndex`/`writeKnowledgeOption` for the respective dirs, plus `writeEventFile` for `events/<name>.ts`, `writeHookFile` for `hooks/<slug>.ts`, and `writeManifest` for `package.json`; existing space files are read back with `readSpaceFile`/`listSpaceDir` `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md:5-18` · `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/functions/writeEventFile.ts#writeEventFile`.\n41\t\n42\t## How an agent wires up\n43\t\n44\t```mermaid\n45\tflowchart TD\n46\t  AG[\"agents/&lt;slug&gt;/<br/>charter.md + instruct.md\"]\n47\t  AG -->|\"functions:\"| FN[\"functions/&lt;fn&gt;.ts<br/>deterministic helpers\"]\n48\t  AG -->|\"knowledge:\"| KN[\"knowledge/&lt;domain&gt;/&lt;field&gt;/<br/>load-on-demand docs\"]\n49\t  AG -->|\"components:\"| CP[\"components/{view,form}/&lt;Name&gt;.tsx\"]\n50\t  AG -->|\"actions[ ].tasklist\"| TL[\"tasklists/&lt;slug&gt;/<br/>index.md + NN-*.md DAG\"]\n51\t  AG -->|\"capabilities:\"| CAP[\"db / pages / api / hooks<br/>project-app grants\"]\n52\t  AG -->|\"canDelegateTo:\"| OTHER[\"other agents / spaces\"]\n53\t  EV[\"events/&lt;name&gt;.ts<br/>emitter defs\"] -->|\"message.received …\"| BUS([\"event bus\"])\n54\t```\n55\t\n56\tAn agent's `instruct.md` frontmatter names its tooling, and every key is checked against a fail-loud allow-list (`title, knowledge, functions, components, actions, defaultAction, canDelegateTo, dependencies, capabilities, model, triggers`) so a typo throws rather than silently granting nothing `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts#AGENT_FRONTMATTER_ALLOWED_KEYS,461-466`. `loadSpace` then validates each reference against the sibling directory, verifying **every edge** in the diagram above:\n57\t\n58\t- **`functions:`** — each name must exist in `functions/`, else a load-time throw `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:684-691`; the source is loaded by `loadFunctionsFromDir` from `functions/*.ts` `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts#loadFunctionsFromDir`.\n59\t- **`knowledge:`** — a `<domain>/<field>[/<option>]` ref is split and each segment must resolve in the `knowledge/` tree `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:699-718`; the tree is `knowledge/<domain>/<field>/` where `index.md` frontmatter carries `type/variable/default/description` and every other `.md` is an aspect option `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts#loadKnowledge`.\n60\t- **`components:`** — each name must exist in `components/view` or `components/form`, else a throw `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:692-698`; both directories are read one `<Name>.tsx` per component `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts#loadComponents`.\n61\t- **`actions[].tasklist`** — each action's `tasklist` must name a loaded tasklist directory, else a throw `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:662-670`; tasklists are `tasklists/<slug>/` with an `index.md` header plus lexically-sorted `NN-<id>.md` step files `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts#loadTasklists`.\n62\t- **`capabilities:`** — parsed into the project-app grant set (`db:*`/`pages:write`/`api:write`/`hooks:write`/…) by `parseCapabilities` `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:468` · `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/capabilities.ts` `parseCapabilities`.\n63\t- **`canDelegateTo:`** — the delegation allowlist (falls back to the deprecated `dependencies` key) `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:477-481`.\n64\t- **`events/*.ts`** — a default-exported typed `EmitterDef` (`webhook`/`cron`/`db`/`internal`) that makes the space an **event source** on the bus `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/emitter-def.ts` `EmitterDef`; e.g. the Slack space's `events/messages.ts` emits a normalized `message.received` from Slack's verified `event_callback` `store/spaces/integration-slack/events/messages.ts:1-20`.\n65\t\n66\t`charter.md` and `instruct.md` are the two agent files: the charter is read body-only (no frontmatter required) `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts:548-553`, and the system prompt renders the charter (`# Agent`) before the instructions (`# Agent Instructions`), then the actions list `sdk/org/libs/core/src/context/system-block.ts:229-242`.\n67\t\n68\t### A real agent's frontmatter (adapted)\n69\t\n70\tEvery reference below points at a sibling directory of the `newsroom` space `store/projects/blog/spaces/newsroom/agents/researcher/instruct.md:1-16`:\n71\t\n72\t```yaml\n73\ttitle: Researcher\n74\tdefaultAction: deep-dive\n75\tactions:\n76\t  - id: deep-dive\n77\t    label: Deep dive\n78\t    description: Produce a grounded deep-dive research report.\n79\t    tasklist: deep-dive              # → tasklists/deep-dive/\n80\tknowledge:\n81\t  - journalism/deep-dive-method      # → knowledge/journalism/deep-dive-method/\n82\tcomponents:\n83\t  - ResearchPreview                  # → components/view/ResearchPreview.tsx\n84\tcapabilities:\n85\t  - db:read:  { tables: [articles, citations, research] }\n86\t  - db:write: { tables: [research] }\n87\t```\n88\t\n89\t## Per-file-kind docs\n90\t\n91\t| File | Doc |\n92\t|---|---|\n93\t| `package.json` (`lmthing` block) | [package.json.md](./package.json.md) |\n94\t| `agents/<slug>/charter.md` + `instruct.md` | [agents/](./agents/README.md) |\n95\t| `functions/<fn>.ts` | [functions/](./functions/README.md) |\n96\t| `components/{view,form}/<Name>.tsx` | [components/](./components/README.md) |\n97\t| `tasklists/<slug>/index.md` + `NN-<id>.md` | [tasklists/](./tasklists/README.md) |\n98\t| `knowledge/<domain>/<field>/index.md` + `<aspect>.md` | [knowledge/](./knowledge/README.md) |\n99\t| `events/<name>.ts` | [events/](./events/README.md) |\n100\t| `hooks/<slug>.ts` (event consumers) | [hooks/](./hooks/README.md) |\n101\t\n102\tThe `events/`/`hooks/` pair is the same unified event pipeline used by projects — see the project side at [../project/events/](../project/events/README.md) and [../project/hooks/](../project/hooks/README.md).\n103\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"07505bfe-a0f1-4aee-a3f1-2914d0a4ae88","uuid":"68c2564c-3f81-4c48-a9d7-f64e8f6fb874","timestamp":"2026-07-14T17:16:08.161Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/format/space/README.md","content":"# `space/` — space format\n\nA **space** is a directory bundle of AI specialists (**agents**) plus the tooling they reference; `loa